RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1 1/8M Turf CR: 92. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, if for $50,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHADOW CREEK (IRE) rated in the two path, bid three deep on the far turn, bumped at the top of the lane, took over in upper stretch, fought with PLAYER B in the furlong grounds and held gamely. PLAYER B unhurried in the beginning and moved into the two path, tipped out on the far turn, rallied and fought outside of SHADOW CREEK (IRE) in the furlong grounds but could not go by. CRYPTO MAN broke a step slow then settled inside, tipped two wide on the far turn but lacked room behind a wall of rivals, angled out in the lane, bid three deep and finished a game third. QUINTECENTS stalked along the rail, waited for room on the far turn, lacked room in upper stretch, gained a clear path and churned on for a minor award. NOBEL GARY brushed the gate, pulled to the front then moved inside, set the pace along the rail to the far turn, pressured around that bend, lost command in upper stretch and weakened. HARD TIMES rated in the two path, closest in pursuit from outside up the backstretch, challenged on the far turn, bumped with rival at the top of the lane and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE SMOKIN MOON raced up close outside the top pair, took aim three wide into the stretch, challenged with a furlong remaining, had the rider lose his whip midstretch, dug in under strong handling and prevailed. ROSIE ANN RULES settled early outside a rival, rounded the bend three deep, drifted inward in upper stretch, rallied between in deep stretch but was too late. ELTONSINGSANOTHER dueled for the lead from inside, put a head in front on the turn, fought with ONE SMOKIN MOON entering the final furlong, lost the lead shortly after and stayed on gamely while getting edged for second. JUST IS threw her head at the start then bumped with CHEVY GIRL three times, raced four wide at the back into the turn, chased outside inner trio around the bend and summoned a mild response once straightened away in the lane. CHEVY GIRL bumped with JUST IS repeatedly leaving the gate, started to climb and was steered down to the inside, saved ground through the turn and kept on trying through the drive but was unable to threaten. COME JOIN THE BAND got bumped outward leaving the gate, went up to take control then dueled with inner rival, fought two wide through the turn, could not kick on with the ELTONSINGSANOTHER approaching the eighth pole and weakened after. SMILING AMY veered out and bumped at the start, chased off the pace out of range, raced between rivals or two wide on the turn and also weakened in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT ROD MAMA broke a step slow, unhurried in the beginning and lagged behind, trailed along the inside into the turn, tipped out approaching the quarter pole, spun three wide into the lane, rallied while drifted inward on the wrong lead, drew alongside BARBERA in the final sixteenth and drove past. SUGAR SUGAR got knocked into outer rival leaving the gate, sat off the pace early, rounded the bend three then two wide, showed a mild response going between foes in the lane and finished evenly late for a clear third. ROSE GIRL veered out and bumped SUGAR SUGAR at the start, cleared quickly and showed the way to the turn, pressured by BARBERA around the turn, fought two wide into the lane, yielded in upper stretch and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 83. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, if for $50,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred). (Rail a t 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAHINA unhurried and moved into the two path, trailed on the inside into the far turn, swung out past the quarter pole, surged widest and got up. PRINCESS MIDNIGHT showed good early foot to establish the front, set all the pace on the inside to the stretch, met the bid from PORT ELLEN (IRE) in upper stretch, maintained command into the final sixteenth but had no answer for MAHINA in the closing moments. PORT ELLEN (IRE) stalked from inside, tipped two wide leaving the far turn, challenged PRINCESS MIDNIGHT from outside in upper stretch failed to find the needed late kick. VIEWERS DISCRETION stalked in the the two path then between rivals, eased out on the far turn and came four wide into the lane, shifted in to bump rival in upper stretch and kept on for a minor award. HAPPYASACLAM (IRE) was closest in pursuit early on in the two path, took aim three wide entering the lane, got bumped by VIEWERS DISCRETION in upper stretch and faltered late. NICELY CURVED forwardly placed early and got fanned four wide into the first turn, moved into the three path around the bend, rounded the far turn two then three wide, angled out then back inward in upper stretch and lacked a rally. CHRISTINA'S CANDY was off slow to begin, settled inside, cut the corner into the stretch and weakened. VULIN tracked three deep early, started to weaken under coaxing three wide on the far turn, trailed four wide into the lane and had little left for the stretch run. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE STRETCH RUN AND AFTER A REVIEW RULED THAT VIEWERS DISCRETION AND HAPPYASACLAM (IRE) BOTH CONTRIBUTED TO THE INCIDENT AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 78. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY LITHESOME broke a step slow then was content to sit off the pace early and moved into the two path, angled out while on the move on the far turn, spun four wide into the lane, got bumped in upper stretch, floated out a bit past the eighth pole, rallied to the front approaching the sixteenth pole and drove clear. KITZKATY settled three then two wide outside a rival, moved closer between foes on the far turn, waited for room behind the leaders with a quarter mile left to run, shifted out and bumped rival in upper stretch, altered in at the eighth pole and kept on to get up for second. ASADA FRIES dueled for the lead from inside, fought through the far turn and into the lane, cleared in upper stretch, relinquished the lead outside the sixteenth pole and got edged for second. O K ROSE settled inside then had to steady when running up behind a rival into the backstretch, raced inside a rival off the pace in the middle stages, lacked room past the three-eighths pole, found traffic again briefly in upper stretch, altered to the inside and finished willingly to round out the superfecta. BEAUTIFUL JANET dueled outside a rival into the first turn, drifted out and had to be reined in while continuing to fight for the lead and racing keenly, battled through the far turn and into the stretch, got floated out at the eighth pole and flattened. EBOK'S DREAM GIRL chased two wide into the first turn, had to take up when outer rival crossed in front early on the clubhouse bend, traveled in mid-pack up the backstretch, went three wide into the far turn, moved out and exited the bend five deep, was forced to check behind rivals in upper stretch and could not rally. WAILEA SUNSET was off slow to begin, trailed on the inside early, moved out and went four wide into the far turn, altered out in upper stretch and failed to make an impact. LOOKATHERGLIDE pulled three wide into the first turn, steadied and shifted into the two path bothering rivals, was closest in pursuit of the top pair up the backstretch, took aim three wide into the lane, got pinballed in upper stretch and was not persevered with after. COCKTAIL CUTIE rated on the inside, had to check when put in tight by LOOKATHERGLIDE early on the clubhouse turn, moved closer up the backstretch, saved ground to the lane and faded. THE RIDER ABOARD LOOKATHERGLIDE LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST KITZKATY FOR INTERFERENCE IN UPPER STRETCH AND THERE WAS ALSO A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE SAME INCIDENT. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED KITZKATY FROM SECOND TO EIGHTH FOR SHIFTING OUT AND COSTING LOOKATHERGLIDE A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.
